JDK (www.oracle.com)
	1. Java JDK (8)
	2. JAVA_HOME
	3. path

Tomcat (tomcat.apache.org)
	1. Tomcat core zip (7)
	2. link Eclipse

Eclipse (www.eclipse.org)
	1. Eclipse Java EE IDE (Mars)
	2. workspace
	3. Tomcat settings (server double click)
		server location : use tomcat installation
		server option : public module contexts to separate XML files
		ports : http 8181 (oracle db)
	4. project
		dynamic web project
		target runtime : apache tomcat
		generate web.xml deployment descriptor : check

Git
	1. dynamic web project git project managment doesn't work, workaround
		copy contents, dynamic web project(work) <-> resource project(git save)
	2. load project
		pull git repository
		create resource project from git
		create dynamic web project
		copy contents, resource->dynamic web project
			src -> Java Resources src
			files ->	WebContent
	3. save project
		copy contents, dynamic web->resource project
			Java Resources src -> src
			WebContent -> files
		commit&push git repository
